de.ovgu.featureide.fm.core.base.impl

Class Feature

  • All Implemented Interfaces:

    Direct Known Subclasses:
    ExtendedFeature

    public class Feature
extends AFeature
    Implementation of AFeature used as default implementation inside FeatureIDE.

    This class implements the functionality required by IFeature and a AFeatureModelElement, specified in AFeature.

    This class is intended to be the default implementation for regular use-cases of feature management. Further specialization for other use-cases is available in the sub classes ExtendedFeature and inside SXFMReader.

    An instance of a Feature is intended to be instantiated by a IFeatureModelFactory.

    Example
    The following example demonstrate the creation of a new feature called FeatureA using FeatureIDE's default IFeature ( AFeature) implementation Feature, and the corresponding default factory DefaultFeatureModelFactory over the conviennent factory class FMFactoryManager. The instance is stored against the IFeature interface: IFeatureModel model = FMFactoryManager.getFactory().createFeatureModel(); IFeature feature = FMFactoryManager.getFactory().createFeature(model, "FeatureA"); A unified handling of certain Feature (AFeature, IFeature) implementations (in terms of conviennent methods) can be achieved with the use of FeatureUtils helper class.
    Since:
    3.0
    Author:
    Thomas Thuem, Sebastian Krieter, Marcus Pinnecke

        public IFeature clone(IFeatureModel newFeatureModel,
                      IFeatureStructure newStructure)
        Description copied from interface: IFeature
        Creates a new instance (new reference) of this feature with the same feature name and internal id, optionally change the features feature model and/or structure.
        Parameters:
        newFeatureModel - A new feature model in which the feature should be part of. If this parameter is null, the cloned feature's new feature model have to be the originals feature's feature model.
        newStructure - A new structure in which the feature should life. If this parameter is null, the cloned feature's new structure have to be the originals feature's structure.
        Returns:
        New instance f' of this feature f such that f != f' but f.equals(f') holds.
